The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Sunday, December 19, 2004 

 Couple held for son?s death

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Krishnagar (Nadia), Dec. 18: The parents, brother and sister-in law of a businessman were arrested on Saturday for their alleged links in the brutal killing of the 35-year-old.

 The accused sprinkled acid all over the body of Nirmal Bhowmik in Nabadwip, according to preliminary investigation.

 They then tried to portray the man?s death as suicide, saying he was suffering from depression.

 Police swung into action after the victim?s wife, Haripriya, lodged a complaint with Nabadwip police station.

 ?After receiving the complaint, we set up a medical team and doctors found there were a number injury marks on Bhowmik?s body. Besides, we have got more vital leads indicating that it was not a case of suicide,? said Benoy Chakrabarty , superintendent of police, Nadia. 




